The paper discusses the Second Workshop on Sustainable Software for Science, which focuses on software engineering practices and experiences in scientific research. The topics covered include exploring sustainability, software development experiences, credit & incentives, reproducibility & reuse & sharing, and code testing & code review. These topics are all related to software engineering and development, which are covered in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category. Additionally, the paper discusses metrics for research software, which could fall under the Cybernetics (cs.CY), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), or Mathematical Software (cs.MS) categories.
